Name: -të
Comment: Only occurs on a few nouns.

Name: -sapë
Comment: From [mp](sapenmlz). Only occurs on the copula.

Name: -topo
Comment: Contained in [mp](tojpepurp). Marginally occurs in predicative uses (histyarirdi-0542, histyarirdi-0091); can combine with [mp](neinf).

Name: t-
Comment: Fossilized, but still looks like a morpheme.

Name: -jtë
Comment: n>vt, ‘provide P with N’ or ‘make P characterized by N’

Name: tawaja
Comment: Looks suspiciously like [mp](tawara-too) and [mp](janeg), but the combination would be unexpected.

Name: jra
Comment: From PC \*_pïra_; usually occurs as an enclitic on verbs, nouns and adverbials.
